{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm an American, which means, generally,"},{"time":3000,"text":"I ignore football unless it involves"},{"time":5000,"text":"guys my size or Bruno's size"},{"time":7000,"text":"running into each other at extremely high speeds."},{"time":10000,"text":"That said, it's been really hard"},{"time":12000,"text":"to ignore football"},{"time":14000,"text":"for the last couple of weeks."},{"time":16000,"text":"I go onto Twitter, there are all these strange words that I've never heard before:"},{"time":19000,"text":"FIFA, vuvuzela,"},{"time":21000,"text":"weird jokes about octopi."},{"time":23000,"text":"But the one that's really been sort of stressing me out,"},{"time":25000,"text":"that I haven't been able to figure out,"},{"time":27000,"text":"is this phrase \"Cala a boca, Galvao.\""},{"time":29000,"text":"If you've gone onto Twitter in the last couple of weeks,"},{"time":31000,"text":"you've probably seen this."},{"time":33000,"text":"It's been a major trending topic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"Being a monolingual American, I obviously don't know what the phrase means."},{"time":38000,"text":"So I went onto Twitter,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and I asked some people if they could explain to me \"Cala a boca, Galvao.\""},{"time":43000,"text":"And fortunately, my Brazilian friends"},{"time":45000,"text":"were more than ready to help."},{"time":47000,"text":"They explained that the Galvao bird"},{"time":50000,"text":"is a rare and endangered parrot"},{"time":52000,"text":"that's in terrible, terrible danger."},{"time":54000,"text":"In fact, I'll let them tell you a bit more about it."},{"time":56000,"text":"Narrator: A word about Galvao, a very rare kind of bird"},{"time":59000,"text":"native to Brazil."},{"time":61000,"text":"Every year, more than 300,000 Galvao birds"},{"time":64000,"text":"are killed during Carnival parades."},{"time":66000,"text":"Ethan Zuckerman: Obviously, this is a tragic situation,"},{"time":68000,"text":"and it actually gets worse."},{"time":70000,"text":"It turns out that, not only is the Galvao parrot"},{"time":72000,"text":"very attractive, useful for headdresses,"},{"time":75000,"text":"it evidently has certain hallucinogenic properties,"},{"time":78000,"text":"which means that there's a terrible problem"},{"time":80000,"text":"with Galvao abuse."},{"time":82000,"text":"Some sick and twisted people have found themselves snorting Galvao."},{"time":85000,"text":"And it's terribly endangered."},{"time":87000,"text":"The good news about this is that the global community --"},{"time":89000,"text":"again, my Brazilian friends tell me --"},{"time":91000,"text":"is pitching in to help out."},{"time":93000,"text":"It turns out that Lady Gaga"},{"time":95000,"text":"has released a new single --"},{"time":97000,"text":"actually five or six new singles, as near as I can tell --"},{"time":100000,"text":"titled \"Cala a boca, Galvao.\""},{"time":102000,"text":"And my Brazilian friends tell me that"},{"time":104000,"text":"if I just tweet the phrase \"Cala a boca, Galvao,\""},{"time":106000,"text":"10 cents will be given"},{"time":108000,"text":"to a global campaign"},{"time":110000,"text":"to save this rare and beautiful bird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113000,"text":"Now, most of you have figured out that this was a prank,"},{"time":115000,"text":"and actually a very, very good one."},{"time":117000,"text":"\"Cala a boca, Galvao\" actually means something very different."},{"time":119000,"text":"In Portugese, it means \"Shut your mouth, Galvao.\""},{"time":122000,"text":"And it specifically refers to this guy, Galvao Bueno,"},{"time":125000,"text":"who's the lead soccer commentator"},{"time":127000,"text":"for Rede Globo."},{"time":129000,"text":"And what I understand from my Brazilian friends"},{"time":131000,"text":"is that this guy is just a cliche machine."},{"time":134000,"text":"He can ruin the most interesting match"},{"time":137000,"text":"by just spouting cliche again and again and again."},{"time":139000,"text":"So Brazilians went to that first match"},{"time":141000,"text":"against North Korea,"},{"time":143000,"text":"put up this banner, started a Twitter campaign"},{"time":145000,"text":"and tried to convince the rest of us"},{"time":147000,"text":"to tweet the phrase: \"Cala a boca, Galvao.\""},{"time":149000,"text":"And in fact, were so successful at this"},{"time":152000,"text":"that it topped Twitter for two weeks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"Now there's a couple --"},{"time":156000,"text":"there's a couple of lessons that you can take from this."},{"time":159000,"text":"And the first lesson, which I think is a worthwhile one,"},{"time":162000,"text":"is that you cannot go wrong"},{"time":164000,"text":"asking people to be active online,"},{"time":166000,"text":"so long as activism just means retweeting a phrase."},{"time":169000,"text":"So as long as activism is that simple,"},{"time":171000,"text":"it's pretty easy to get away with."},{"time":173000,"text":"The other thing you can take from this, by the way,"},{"time":175000,"text":"is that there are a lot of Brazilians on Twitter."},{"time":178000,"text":"There's more than five million of them."},{"time":180000,"text":"As far as national representation,"},{"time":182000,"text":"11 percent of Brazilian internet users are on Twitter."},{"time":185000,"text":"That's a much higher number than in the U.S. or U.K."},{"time":188000,"text":"Next to Japan,"},{"time":190000,"text":"it's the second most represented by population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"Now if you're using Twitter or other social networks,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and you didn't realize"},{"time":197000,"text":"this was a space with a lot of Brazilians in it,"},{"time":199000,"text":"you're like most of us."},{"time":201000,"text":"Because what happens on a social network"},{"time":203000,"text":"is you interact with the people"},{"time":205000,"text":"that you have chosen to interact with."},{"time":207000,"text":"And if you are like me, a big, geeky, white, American guy,"},{"time":210000,"text":"you tend to interact with a lot of other geeky, white, American guys."},{"time":213000,"text":"And you don't necessarily have the sense"},{"time":215000,"text":"that Twitter is in fact a very heavily Brazilian space."},{"time":217000,"text":"It's also extremely surprising to many Americans,"},{"time":220000,"text":"a heavily African-American space."},{"time":223000,"text":"Twitter recently did some research."},{"time":225000,"text":"They looked at their local population."},{"time":227000,"text":"They believe that 24 percent"},{"time":229000,"text":"of American Twitter users are African-American."},{"time":231000,"text":"That's about twice as high as African-Americans"},{"time":233000,"text":"are represented in the population."},{"time":235000,"text":"And again, that was very shocking to many Twitter users,"},{"time":237000,"text":"but it shouldn't be."},{"time":239000,"text":"And the reason it shouldn't be is that on any day"},{"time":241000,"text":"you can go into Trending Topics."},{"time":243000,"text":"And you tend to find topics"},{"time":245000,"text":"that are almost entirely African-American conversations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249000,"text":"This was a visualization done by Fernando Viegas"},{"time":251000,"text":"and Martin Wattenberg,"},{"time":253000,"text":"two amazing visualization designers,"},{"time":255000,"text":"who looked at"},{"time":257000,"text":"a weekend's worth of Twitter traffic"},{"time":259000,"text":"and essentially found that a lot of these trending topics"},{"time":261000,"text":"were basically segregated conversations --"},{"time":264000,"text":"and in ways that you wouldn't expect."},{"time":266000,"text":"It turns out that oil spill is a mostly white conversation,"},{"time":269000,"text":"that cookout"},{"time":271000,"text":"is a mostly black conversation."},{"time":273000,"text":"And what's crazy about this is that"},{"time":275000,"text":"if you wanted to mix up who you were seeing on Twitter,"},{"time":278000,"text":"it's literally a quick click away."},{"time":281000,"text":"You click on that cookout tag, there an entirely different conversation"},{"time":283000,"text":"with different people participating in it."},{"time":286000,"text":"But generally speaking, most of us don't."},{"time":288000,"text":"We end up within these filter bubbles, as my friend Eli Pariser calls them,"},{"time":291000,"text":"where we see the people we already know"},{"time":293000,"text":"and the people who are similar to the people we already know."},{"time":296000,"text":"And we tend not to see that wider picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"Now for me, I'm surprised by this,"},{"time":302000,"text":"because this wasn't how the internet was supposed to be."},{"time":305000,"text":"If you go back into the early days of the internet,"},{"time":307000,"text":"when cyber-utopians like Nick Negroponte"},{"time":310000,"text":"were writing big books like \"Being Digital,\""},{"time":312000,"text":"the prediction was that the internet"},{"time":314000,"text":"was going to be an incredibly powerful force"},{"time":316000,"text":"to smooth out cultural differences,"},{"time":319000,"text":"to put us all on a common field of one fashion or another."},{"time":322000,"text":"Negroponte started his book with a story"},{"time":325000,"text":"about how hard it is to build connections"},{"time":327000,"text":"in the world of atoms."},{"time":329000,"text":"He's at a technology conference in Florida."},{"time":331000,"text":"And he's looking at something really, truly absurd,"},{"time":334000,"text":"which is bottles of Evian water on the table."},{"time":337000,"text":"And Negroponte says this is crazy."},{"time":339000,"text":"This is the old economy."},{"time":341000,"text":"It's the economy of moving these"},{"time":343000,"text":"heavy, slow atoms over long distances that's very difficult to do."},{"time":346000,"text":"We're heading to the future of bits,"},{"time":348000,"text":"where everything is speedy, it's weightless."},{"time":350000,"text":"It can be anywhere in the world at any time."},{"time":352000,"text":"And it's going to change the world as we know it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"Now, Negroponte has been right about a lot of things."},{"time":357000,"text":"He's totally wrong about this one."},{"time":359000,"text":"It turns out that in many cases"},{"time":361000,"text":"atoms are much more mobile than bits."},{"time":364000,"text":"If I walk into a store in the United States,"},{"time":366000,"text":"it's very, very easy for me to buy water"},{"time":369000,"text":"that's bottled in Fiji,"},{"time":371000,"text":"shipped at great expense to the United States."},{"time":373000,"text":"It's actually surprisingly hard"},{"time":376000,"text":"for me to see a Fijian feature film."},{"time":378000,"text":"It's really difficult for me to listen to Fijian music."},{"time":381000,"text":"It's extremely difficult for me to get Fijian news,"},{"time":384000,"text":"which is strange, because actually there's an enormous amount going on in Fiji."},{"time":387000,"text":"There's a coup government. There's a military government."},{"time":389000,"text":"There's crackdowns on the press."},{"time":391000,"text":"It's actually a place that we probably should"},{"time":393000,"text":"be paying attention to at the moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"Here's what I think is going on."},{"time":397000,"text":"I think that we tend to look a lot"},{"time":399000,"text":"at the infrastructure"},{"time":401000,"text":"of globalization."},{"time":403000,"text":"We look at the framework that makes it possible"},{"time":405000,"text":"to live in this connected world."},{"time":407000,"text":"And that's a framework that includes things like airline routes."},{"time":410000,"text":"It includes things like the Internet cables."},{"time":412000,"text":"We look at a map like this one,"},{"time":414000,"text":"and it looks like the entire world is flat"},{"time":417000,"text":"because everything is a hop or two away."},{"time":419000,"text":"You can get on a flight in London,"},{"time":421000,"text":"you can end up in Bangalore later today."},{"time":423000,"text":"Two hops, you're in Suva, the capitol of Fiji."},{"time":425000,"text":"It's all right there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"When you start looking at what actually"},{"time":429000,"text":"flows on top of these networks,"},{"time":431000,"text":"you get a very different picture."},{"time":433000,"text":"You start looking at how"},{"time":435000,"text":"the global plane flights move,"},{"time":437000,"text":"and you suddenly discover that the world isn't even close to flat."},{"time":439000,"text":"It's extremely lumpy."},{"time":441000,"text":"There are parts of the world that are very, very well connected."},{"time":443000,"text":"There's basically a giant pathway in the sky"},{"time":445000,"text":"between London and New York."},{"time":447000,"text":"but look at this map, and you can watch this"},{"time":449000,"text":"for, you know, two or three minutes."},{"time":451000,"text":"You won't see very many planes"},{"time":453000,"text":"go from South America to Africa."},{"time":455000,"text":"And you'll discover that there are parts of the globe"},{"time":457000,"text":"that are systematically cut off."},{"time":459000,"text":"When we stop looking at the infrastructure that makes connection possible,"},{"time":462000,"text":"and we look at what actually happens,"},{"time":465000,"text":"we start realizing that the world doesn't work quite the same way"},{"time":467000,"text":"that we think it does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"So here's the problem that I've been interested in"},{"time":471000,"text":"in the last decade or so."},{"time":474000,"text":"The world is, in fact, getting more global."},{"time":476000,"text":"It's getting more connected."},{"time":478000,"text":"More of problems are global in scale."},{"time":480000,"text":"More of our economics is global in scale."},{"time":482000,"text":"And our media is less global by the day."},{"time":485000,"text":"If you watched a television broadcast in the United States in the 1970s,"},{"time":488000,"text":"35 to 40 percent of it would have been international news"},{"time":491000,"text":"on a nightly new broadcast."},{"time":493000,"text":"That's down to about 12 to 15 percent."},{"time":496000,"text":"And this tends to give us a very distorted view of the world."},{"time":499000,"text":"Here's a slide that Alisa Miller showed at a previous TED Talk."},{"time":502000,"text":"Alisa's the president of Public Radio International."},{"time":505000,"text":"And she made a cartogram, which is basically a distorted map"},{"time":508000,"text":"based on what American"},{"time":510000,"text":"television news casts"},{"time":512000,"text":"looked at for a month."},{"time":514000,"text":"And you see that when you distort a map based on attention,"},{"time":517000,"text":"the world within American television news"},{"time":519000,"text":"is basically reduced to"},{"time":521000,"text":"this giant bloated U.S."},{"time":523000,"text":"and a couple of other countries which we've invaded."},{"time":525000,"text":"And that's basically what our media is about."},{"time":528000,"text":"And before you conclude that this is just a function of American TV news --"},{"time":531000,"text":"which is dreadful, and I agree that it's dreadful --"},{"time":534000,"text":"I've been mapping elite media like the New York Times,"},{"time":536000,"text":"and I get the same thing."},{"time":538000,"text":"When you look at the New York Times, you look at other elite media,"},{"time":540000,"text":"what you largely get are pictures of very wealthy nations"},{"time":543000,"text":"and the nations we've invaded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545000,"text":"It turns out that new media"},{"time":547000,"text":"isn't necessarily helping us all that much."},{"time":549000,"text":"Here's a map made by Mark Graham"},{"time":551000,"text":"who's down the street at the Oxford Internet Institute."},{"time":553000,"text":"A this is a map of articles in Wikipedia"},{"time":555000,"text":"that have been geo-coded."},{"time":557000,"text":"And you'll notice that there's a very heavy bias"},{"time":559000,"text":"towards North America and Western Europe."},{"time":562000,"text":"Even within Wikipedias,"},{"time":564000,"text":"where we're creating their own content online,"},{"time":566000,"text":"there's a heavy bias towards the place where"},{"time":568000,"text":"a lot of the Wikipedia authors are based,"},{"time":570000,"text":"rather than to the rest of the world."},{"time":572000,"text":"In the U.K., you can get up,"},{"time":574000,"text":"you can pick up your computer when you get out of this session,"},{"time":576000,"text":"you could read a newspaper from India or from Australia,"},{"time":578000,"text":"from Canada, God forbid from the U.S."},{"time":581000,"text":"You probably won't."},{"time":583000,"text":"If you look at online media consumption --"},{"time":585000,"text":"in this case, in the top 10 users of the internet --"},{"time":588000,"text":"more than 95 percent of the news readership"},{"time":590000,"text":"is on domestic news sites."},{"time":592000,"text":"It's one of these rare cases where the U.S. is actually slightly better than [the U.K.],"},{"time":595000,"text":"because we actually like reading your media,"},{"time":597000,"text":"rather than vice versa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599000,"text":"So all of this starts leading me"},{"time":601000,"text":"to think that we're in a state that I refer to"},{"time":603000,"text":"as imaginary cosmopolitanism."},{"time":605000,"text":"We look at the internet."},{"time":607000,"text":"We think we're getting this wide view of the globe."},{"time":610000,"text":"We occasionally stumble onto a page in Chinese,"},{"time":612000,"text":"and we decide that we do in fact have the greatest technology ever built"},{"time":615000,"text":"to connect us to the rest of the world."},{"time":617000,"text":"And we forget that most of the time"},{"time":619000,"text":"we're checking Boston Red Sox scores."},{"time":622000,"text":"So this is a real problem --"},{"time":624000,"text":"not just because the Red Sox are having a bad year --"},{"time":627000,"text":"but it's a real problem because,"},{"time":629000,"text":"as we're discussing here at TED,"},{"time":631000,"text":"the real problems in the world"},{"time":633000,"text":"the interesting problems to solve"},{"time":635000,"text":"are global in scale and scope,"},{"time":637000,"text":"they require global conversations"},{"time":639000,"text":"to get to global solutions."},{"time":641000,"text":"This is a problem we have to solve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643000,"text":"So here's the good news."},{"time":645000,"text":"For six years, I've been hanging out with these guys."},{"time":647000,"text":"This is a group called Global Voices."},{"time":649000,"text":"This is a team of bloggers from around the world."},{"time":651000,"text":"Our mission was to fix the world's media."},{"time":654000,"text":"We started in 2004."},{"time":656000,"text":"You might have noticed, we haven't done all that well so far."},{"time":658000,"text":"Nor do I think we are by ourselves,"},{"time":660000,"text":"actually going to solve the problem."},{"time":662000,"text":"But the more that I think about it, the more that I think"},{"time":664000,"text":"that a few things that we have learned along the way"},{"time":667000,"text":"are interesting lessons for how we would rewire"},{"time":670000,"text":"if we we wanted to use the web to have a wider world."},{"time":673000,"text":"The first thing you have to consider"},{"time":675000,"text":"is that there are parts of the world"},{"time":677000,"text":"that are dark spots in terms of attention."},{"time":679000,"text":"In this case -- the map of the world at night by NASA --"},{"time":682000,"text":"they're dark literally because of lack of electricity."},{"time":685000,"text":"And I used to think that a dark spot on this map"},{"time":687000,"text":"basically meant you're not going to get media from there"},{"time":689000,"text":"because there are more basic needs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691000,"text":"What I'm starting to realize is that"},{"time":693000,"text":"you can get media, it's just an enormous amount of work,"},{"time":696000,"text":"and you need an enormous amount of encouragement."},{"time":698000,"text":"One of those dark spots is Madagascar,"},{"time":700000,"text":"a country which is generally better known for the Dreamworks film"},{"time":703000,"text":"than it is actually known for"},{"time":705000,"text":"the lovely people who live there."},{"time":707000,"text":"And so the people who founded"},{"time":709000,"text":"Foko Club in Madagascar"},{"time":711000,"text":"weren't actually concerned with trying to change the image of their country."},{"time":714000,"text":"They were doing something much simpler."},{"time":716000,"text":"It was a club to learn English"},{"time":718000,"text":"and to learn computers and the internet."},{"time":720000,"text":"but what happened was that Madagascar"},{"time":723000,"text":"went through a violent coup."},{"time":725000,"text":"Most independent media was shut down."},{"time":727000,"text":"And the high school students"},{"time":729000,"text":"who were learning to blog through Foko Club"},{"time":731000,"text":"suddenly found themselves talking to an international audience"},{"time":733000,"text":"about the demonstrations, the violence,"},{"time":735000,"text":"everything that was going on within this country."},{"time":738000,"text":"So a very, very small program"},{"time":740000,"text":"designed to get people in front of computers,"},{"time":743000,"text":"publishing their own thoughts, publishing independent media,"},{"time":746000,"text":"ended up having a huge impact"},{"time":748000,"text":"on what we know about this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"Now the trick with this is that I'm guessing"},{"time":752000,"text":"most people here don't speak Malagasy."},{"time":755000,"text":"I'm also guessing that most of you don't even speak Chinese --"},{"time":757000,"text":"which is sort of sad if you think about it,"},{"time":759000,"text":"as it's now the most represented language on the internet."},{"time":761000,"text":"Fortunately people are trying to figure out how to fix this."},{"time":764000,"text":"If you're using Google Chrome and you go to a Chinese language site,"},{"time":767000,"text":"you notice this really cute box at the top,"},{"time":770000,"text":"which automatically detects that the page is in Chinese"},{"time":773000,"text":"and very quickly at a mouse click"},{"time":775000,"text":"will give you a translation of the page."},{"time":777000,"text":"Unfortunately, it's a machine translation of the page."},{"time":780000,"text":"And while Google is very, very good with some languages,"},{"time":782000,"text":"it's actually pretty dreadful with Chinese."},{"time":784000,"text":"And the results can be pretty funny."},{"time":786000,"text":"What you really want -- what I really want,"},{"time":789000,"text":"is eventually the ability to push a button"},{"time":791000,"text":"and have this queued"},{"time":793000,"text":"so a human being can translate this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795000,"text":"And if you think this is absurd, it's not."},{"time":797000,"text":"There's a group right now in China called Yeeyan."},{"time":800000,"text":"And Yeeyan is a group"},{"time":802000,"text":"of 150,000 volunteers"},{"time":804000,"text":"who get online every day."},{"time":806000,"text":"They look for the most interesting content in the English language."},{"time":809000,"text":"They translate roughly 100 articles a day"},{"time":812000,"text":"from major newspapers, major websites."},{"time":814000,"text":"They put it online for free."},{"time":816000,"text":"It's the project of a guy named Zhang Lei,"},{"time":818000,"text":"who was living in the United States during the Lhasa riots"},{"time":821000,"text":"and who couldn't believe how biased"},{"time":823000,"text":"American media coverage was."},{"time":825000,"text":"And he said, \"If there's one thing I can do, I can start translating,"},{"time":828000,"text":"so that people between these countries"},{"time":830000,"text":"start understanding each other a little bit better.\""},{"time":832000,"text":"And my question to you is:"},{"time":834000,"text":"if Yeeyan can line up 150,000 people"},{"time":836000,"text":"to translate the English internet into Chinese,"},{"time":838000,"text":"where's the English language Yeeyan?"},{"time":841000,"text":"Who's going after Chinese,"},{"time":843000,"text":"which now has 400 million internet users out there?"},{"time":846000,"text":"My guess is at least one of them has something interesting to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"So even if we can find a way to translate from Chinese,"},{"time":852000,"text":"there's no guarantee that we're going to find it."},{"time":854000,"text":"When we look for information online,"},{"time":856000,"text":"we basically have two strategies."},{"time":859000,"text":"We use a lot of search."},{"time":861000,"text":"And search is terrific if you know what you're looking for."},{"time":864000,"text":"But if what you're looking for is serendipity,"},{"time":866000,"text":"if you want to stumble onto something"},{"time":868000,"text":"that you didn't know you needed,"},{"time":870000,"text":"our main philosophy is to look to our social networks,"},{"time":872000,"text":"to look for our friends."},{"time":874000,"text":"What are they looking at? Maybe we should be looking at it."},{"time":877000,"text":"The problem with this is that essentially"},{"time":879000,"text":"what you end up getting after a while is the wisdom of the flock."},{"time":881000,"text":"You end up flocking with a lot of people"},{"time":883000,"text":"who are probably similar to you,"},{"time":885000,"text":"who have similar interests."},{"time":887000,"text":"And it's very, very hard to get information"},{"time":889000,"text":"from the other flocks, from the other parts of the world"},{"time":892000,"text":"where people getting together and talking about their own interests."},{"time":895000,"text":"To do this, at a certain point,"},{"time":897000,"text":"you need someone to bump you out of your flock and into another flock."},{"time":900000,"text":"You need a guide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902000,"text":"So this is Amira Al Hussaini. She is the Middle East editor for Global Voices."},{"time":905000,"text":"She has one of the hardest jobs in the world."},{"time":907000,"text":"Not only does she have to keep our Israeli and Palestinian contributors"},{"time":909000,"text":"from killing each other,"},{"time":911000,"text":"she has to figure out"},{"time":913000,"text":"what is going to interest you"},{"time":915000,"text":"about the Middle East."},{"time":917000,"text":"And in that sense of trying to get you"},{"time":919000,"text":"out of your normal orbit,"},{"time":921000,"text":"and to try to get you to pay attention"},{"time":923000,"text":"to a story about someone who's"},{"time":925000,"text":"given up smoking for the month of Ramadan,"},{"time":927000,"text":"she has to know something about a global audience."},{"time":930000,"text":"She has to know something about what stories are available."},{"time":932000,"text":"Basically, she's a deejay."},{"time":934000,"text":"She's a skilled human curator"},{"time":936000,"text":"who knows what material is available to her,"},{"time":938000,"text":"who's able to listen to the audience,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and who's able to make a selection"},{"time":942000,"text":"and push people forward in one fashion or another."},{"time":944000,"text":"I don't think this is necessarily an algorithmic process."},{"time":947000,"text":"I think what's great about the internet"},{"time":949000,"text":"is that it actually makes it much easier"},{"time":951000,"text":"for deejays to reach a wider audience."},{"time":953000,"text":"I know Amira."},{"time":955000,"text":"I can ask her what to read."},{"time":957000,"text":"But with the internet, she's in a position where she can"},{"time":959000,"text":"tell a lot of people what to read."},{"time":961000,"text":"And you can listen to her as well,"},{"time":963000,"text":"if this is a way that you're interested in having your web widened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":966000,"text":"So once you start widening like this,"},{"time":968000,"text":"once you start lighting up voices in the dark spots,"},{"time":970000,"text":"once you start translating, once you start curating,"},{"time":973000,"text":"you end up in some really weird places."},{"time":976000,"text":"This is an image from pretty much my favorite blog,"},{"time":978000,"text":"which is AfriGadget."},{"time":980000,"text":"And AfriGadget is a blog that looks"},{"time":982000,"text":"at technology in an Africa context."},{"time":984000,"text":"And specifically, it's looking at a blacksmith"},{"time":987000,"text":"in Kibera in Nairobi,"},{"time":989000,"text":"who is turning the shaft of a Landrover"},{"time":991000,"text":"into a cold chisel."},{"time":993000,"text":"And when you look at this image, you might find yourself going,"},{"time":995000,"text":"\"Why would I conceivably care about this?\""},{"time":998000,"text":"And the truth is, this guy can probably explain this to you."},{"time":1000000,"text":"This is Erik Hersman. You guys may have seen him around the conference."},{"time":1003000,"text":"He goes by the moniker White African."},{"time":1005000,"text":"He's both a very well known American geek,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"but he's also Kenyan; he was born in Sudan, grew up in Kenya."},{"time":1011000,"text":"He is a bridge figure."},{"time":1014000,"text":"He is someone who literally has feet in both worlds --"},{"time":1016000,"text":"one in the world of the African technology community,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"one in the world of the American technology community."},{"time":1021000,"text":"And so he's able to tell a story"},{"time":1024000,"text":"about this blacksmith in Kibera"},{"time":1026000,"text":"and turn it into a story about repurposing technology,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"about innovating from constraint,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"about looking for inspiration based on reusing materials."},{"time":1034000,"text":"He knows one world,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"and he's finding a way to communicate it to another world,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"both of which he has deep connections to."},{"time":1042000,"text":"These bridge figures, I'm pretty well convinced,"},{"time":1045000,"text":"are the future of how we try to make the world wider"},{"time":1047000,"text":"through using the web."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049000,"text":"But the trick with bridges is, ultimately,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"you need someone to cross them."},{"time":1053000,"text":"And that's where we start talking about xenophiles."},{"time":1055000,"text":"So if I found myself in the NFL,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"I suspect I would spend my off-season"},{"time":1060000,"text":"nursing my wounds, enjoying my house, so on and so forth --"},{"time":1063000,"text":"possibly recording a hip-hop album."},{"time":1065000,"text":"Dhani Jones,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"who is the middle linebacker for the Cincinnati Bengals,"},{"time":1070000,"text":"has a slightly different approach to the off-season."},{"time":1073000,"text":"Dhani has a television show."},{"time":1075000,"text":"It's called \"Dhani Tackles the Globe.\""},{"time":1077000,"text":"And every week on this television show,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"Dhani travels to a different nation of the world."},{"time":1082000,"text":"He finds a local sporting team."},{"time":1084000,"text":"He trains with them for a week, and he plays a match with them."},{"time":1087000,"text":"And his reason for this"},{"time":1089000,"text":"is not just that he wants to master Muay Thai boxing."},{"time":1092000,"text":"It's because, for him,"},{"time":1094000,"text":"sport is the language"},{"time":1096000,"text":"that allows him to encounter"},{"time":1098000,"text":"the full width and wonder of the world."},{"time":1101000,"text":"For some of us it might be music. For some of us it might be food."},{"time":1103000,"text":"For a lot of us it might be literature or writing."},{"time":1106000,"text":"But there are all these different techniques"},{"time":1108000,"text":"that allow you to go out and look at the world"},{"time":1111000,"text":"and find your place within it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1113000,"text":"The goal of my Talk here"},{"time":1115000,"text":"is not to persuade the people in this room"},{"time":1117000,"text":"to embrace your xenophilia."},{"time":1119000,"text":"My guess -- given that you're at a conference called TEDGlobal --"},{"time":1122000,"text":"is that most of you are xenophiles,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"whether or not you use that term."},{"time":1127000,"text":"My challenge instead is this."},{"time":1129000,"text":"It's not enough to make the personal decision"},{"time":1132000,"text":"that you want a wider world."},{"time":1134000,"text":"We have to figure out how to rewire"},{"time":1136000,"text":"the systems that we have."},{"time":1138000,"text":"We have to fix our media."},{"time":1140000,"text":"We have to fix the internet. We have to fix our education."},{"time":1143000,"text":"We have to fix our immigration policy."},{"time":1145000,"text":"We need to look at ways"},{"time":1147000,"text":"of creating serendipity,"},{"time":1149000,"text":"of making translation pervasive,"},{"time":1151000,"text":"and we need to find ways to embrace"},{"time":1153000,"text":"and celebrate these bridge figures."},{"time":1155000,"text":"And we need to figure out how to cultivate xenophiles."},{"time":1157000,"text":"That's what I'm trying to do. I need your help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1160000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}